        <section dupnames="feature\ execution\ flow" ids="feature-execution-flow">
            <title>Feature Execution Flow</title>
            <enumerated_list enumtype="arabic" prefix="" suffix=".">
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>The initiator (BMC) indicates that command is to be serviced by firmware by writing 0x80 to
                        SBRMI::InBndMsg_inst7 (SBRMI_x3F). This register must be set to 0x80 after reset.</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>The initiator (BMC) writes the command to SBRMI::InBndMsg_inst0 (SBRMI_x38).</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>For write operations or read operations which require additional addressing information as shown in the table above, the initiator (BMC) writes Command Data In[31:0] to SBRMI::InBndMsg_inst[4:1]     {SBRMI_x3C(MSB):SBRMI_x39(LSB)}.</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>The initiator (BMC) writes 0x01 to SBRMI::SoftwareInterrupt to notify firmware to perform the requested read or write command.</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>Firmware reads the message and performs the defined action.</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>Firmware writes the original command to outbound message register SBRMI::OutBndMsg_inst0 (SBRMI_x30).</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>Firmware will write SBRMI::Status[SwAlertSts]=1 to generate an ALERT (if enabled) to initiator (BMC) to
                        indicate completion of the requested command. Firmware must (if applicable) put the message data into the message registers SBRMI::OutBndMsg_inst[4:1] {SBRMI_x34(MSB):SBRMI_x31(LSB)}.</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>For a read operation, the initiator (BMC) reads the firmware response Command Data Out[31:0] from
                        SBRMI::OutBndMsg_inst[4:1] {SBRMI_x34(MSB):SBRMI_x31(LSB)}.</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>Firmware clears the interrupt on SBRMI::SoftwareInterrupt.</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>BMC must write 1’b1 to SBRMI::Status[SwAlertSts] to clear the ALERT to initiator (BMC). It is recommended to clear the ALERT upon completion of the current mailbox command.</paragraph>
                </list_item>
            </enumerated_list>
        </section>
